Sharp and Carter are currently recruiting for a number of solutions architects
to provide guidance and leadership across a number of high profile programmes
of work.  
  
Role 1  
  
We are seeking a Solution Architect to lead the migration of ICT
infrastructure for a Queensland Government organisation from one entity to
another. As the ideal candidate, you will be responsible for overseeing the
development and review of ICT infrastructure and solution designs, ensuring a
smooth transition of services. Your expertise in foundational ICT solutions,
enterprise application integrations (including O365), and navigating
complexities in merging services across entities will be crucial for success
in this role.  
  
Role 2  
  
As a Solution Architect to contribute to the digital transformation of
regional hospital facilities under a confidential program. You will be
instrumental in developing and reviewing ICT infrastructure and solution
designs, collaborating with various stakeholders including building
contractors, system integrators, and healthcare professionals. Your expertise
in network architecture, unified communications, and experience with managing
contractors in healthcare facility development will be highly regarded.  
**   
** Role 3   
  
We are seeking a Solution Architect to oversee the ICT infrastructure and
solution architecture designs for a network of hospitals covering a specific
geographical area. In this role, you will collaborate with various parties
including building contractors, system integrators, and stakeholders in the
healthcare sector to establish comprehensive ICT infrastructure requirements.
Your expertise in enterprise applications, telehealth solutions, and managing
contractors in healthcare facility redevelopment will be instrumental in
contributing to our team.  
  
For more information please apply now and i will be in touch to discuss the
role and share the PD's

